Recommendation:
We have recommended that the management strictly monitor the liquidation of cash advances. It is further recommended that:
No additional cash advance be given to officials/employees unless the previous cash advances was settled and the liquidating papers were submitted to the auditor for post-audit;
Exert all possible remedies to collect and demand liquidation of cash advances;
The Municipal Accountant should discourage the partial liquidation per cash advance voucher. The balance shall be strictly refunded upon liquidation; and
Require the Municipal Accountant see to it that supporting documents are complete before certifying the Disbursement Voucher and granting payment of cash advances.

We have recommended that the management strictly observe the provisions of COA Circular No. 97-002 in granting of cash advances. Extra effort for the immediate settlement/liquidation of the cash advances especially those granted to elected officials. Issue demand letters in case officials/employees were not able to liquidate immediately their cash advances, if not possible, the following remedial measures maybe resorted to:

Withhold the salaries and/or other benefits as provided for under Section 5.1.3 of COA Circular No. 97-002 and/or;

Appropriate administrative and criminal actions against the official/employee should be undertaken for the liquidation of their cash advances;

No granting of additional cash advances to official/employee unless their previous cash advances were liquidated and limit the grant of cash advance to elected officials for their travelling expenses and allowances only.
